ristians. Presented for the first time in English, these texts provide valuable points of comparison to other liturgical commentaries produced elsewhere in the medieval Christian world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aLord's Supper (Liturgy). 0aLord's SupperxCoptic Church. 4aMedieval Studies. 4aTheology. 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / Ecclesiology.2bisacsh  aAbū al-Barakat ibn Kabar.  aCoptic liturgy.  aCopto-Arabic literature.  aPope Gabriel V.  aRamez Mikhail.  aliturgical commentary.1 aGabriel V, Pope, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKabar, Abū al-Barakāt ibn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMikhail, Arsenius, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aal-Barakāt ibn Kabar, Abū, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aibn Sabbā, Yūḥannā ibn Abī Zakariyyā, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2022 Englishz978311099454408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2022z9783110994537oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311075166640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823298341?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823298341423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823298341/original  a978-3-11-075166-6  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PA